timeline.bodyText:
I find such heavily nested if/else if/else code very hard to grok.
Have you considered moving the two main chunks into handleSuccess and handleError type methods?
Taking the success one as an example, it might look something like:
private void handleSuccess(final InsertResult result) {
      insertsStreamResponseWriter.writeInsertResponse(new InsertAck(result.sequenceNumber()));
     acksSent++;

     if (insertsSent != null && insertsSent == acksSent) {
         close();
         return;
      }

      if (response.writeQueueFull()) {
            if (!drainHandlerSet) {
                 response.drainHandler(v -> {
                     drainHandlerSet = false;
                     checkMakeRequest();
                 });
               drainHandlerSet = true;
            }
            return;
      }

     checkMakeRequest();
}
I find this much easier to follow, as each if block returns, meaning I don't need to scan down the rest of the method to see what else is going to happen.

